-- Campbell sees profit at upper end of forecast
-- 
-- Mon Jun 30, 2008 8:43am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/06/30/us-campbell-outlook-idUSN3039501020080630

 

 CHICAGO  (Reuters) - Campbell Soup Co ( CPB.N ) on Monday said it expects profit for the current fiscal year to be at the upper end of its forecast range and set a $1.2 billion share repurchase program. 

 The company said it now expects earnings for the fiscal year ending August 3 to show an increase around the upper end of a 5 percent to 7 percent range from the adjusted $1.95 it reported for fiscal 2007. (Reporting by  Brad Dorfman , editing by Gerald E. McCormick)